===date:Tue Jan 21 12:25:11 2003
===message:I agree with a lot of your argument, except one specific part.  You ask, "why would we give that much power back to a central government?"  I believe that the states would have had a difficult time governing themselves and interacting with the other states without a central government to pull the country together.  If each state had its own separate government with no standards set by a central government, it is easy to envision that each state's government would have eventually pulled so far away from the other state's governments, that there would be states fighting states before long.  I feel that the central government pulled the country together as one and eliminated the fear of tyranny by creating the very effective checks and balances system, which we still use today.
=========yorg=========
