===message:Your point of view is very much accurate.  However, I based my answer on the idea that the States have just finished fighting a war against the British who ultimately wanted to control every aspect of America.  With that in mind I can imagine the states being reluctant to give away alot of power for the fear of turning into what they had just fought so hard to seperate from.  Remember this new form of Government had not been tried or tested.  I do not beleive America would have been very succesful without a strong national government, Britain had a strong central government also so what would be the assurance that America would not revert back to what they declared independance from.
