===subject:HIST 2110
===from:Chris Comer
===date:Wed Jan 29 15:02:42 2003
===message:I think that it would be hard to say with certainty which way I would lean at that time. However considering that it took a unified group of states under central leadership to defeat the British I am inclined to lean toward the Federalist.  It was a dangerous time in history. France, Spain, England and others all would have liked to control America. If the states had stayed in a loose confederation our protection as a whole would have suffered. A foreign nation such as Spain with an eye on America might gamble that New York would not send aid to Georgia in the event of an invasion. This perception of weakness, real or otherwise, might led to many more conflicts. As an outside invading force I would much rather deal with a number of smaller uncoordinated defense armies than one large organized one.
=========yorg=========
